The phrase was originally legal: see Caec. 81 and 82, with Jordan's n. The historical reference is to the appointment of Pompeius, with extraordinary powers, to take command in the East against the pirates. This command P. pretended to dislike (Dio Cassius 36, 8), a pretence which had the effect of increasing the popular clamour for his appointment and rendering easier the adoption of the law which conferred on lum such unparalleled powers.
